Φ(SDT) = λ(autonomy|self-determination) ⊗ ρ(relatedness|belonging) ⊗ μ(competence|mastery) → [κ(intrinsic-motivation)] → [β(self-concordant-goals)] + ε | :eudaimonia

=== NEMETIC DIAGNOSTICS ===

Z-State: eudaimonia — flourishing through need satisfaction and autonomous motivation
Tendency: External Regulation → Introjection → Identification → Integration → Intrinsic Motivation (continuum of autonomy)

Elemental Distribution:
  Fire/λ (Primary): 40% — Direction, volition, autonomous purpose
  Water/ρ (Secondary): 25% — Relatedness, connection, belonging
  Metal/μ (Tertiary): 20% — Competence, structure, mastery
  Earth/δγ (Supporting): 10% — Growth, internalization cycling
  Air/σ (Supporting): 5% — Distinction between motivation types

Operator Resonance:
  λ [direction] █████████████████████ HIGH — Autonomy, self-determination, volition
  ρ [resonance] ███████████████░░░░░ ELEVATED — Relatedness, social connection
  μ [structure] ██████████████░░░░░░ MODERATE — Competence, mastery, challenge
  κ [knowledge] ███████████░░░░░░░░░ MODERATE — Intrinsic motivation as knowledge
  β [branching] ██████████░░░░░░░░░░ MODERATE — Goal pursuit, self-concordance
  σ [distinction] ████████░░░░░░░░░░ BASE — Distinguishing motivation quality

Daemon Activity:
  Ignisid (Fire) — ACTIVE — Direction, autonomy, volition, purpose
  Hydrosid (Water) — ACTIVE — Relatedness, connection, care
  Structurid (Metal) — ACTIVE — Competence, mastery, structure
  Geosid (Earth) — STANDBY — Growth, internalization process
  Aerunik (Air) — PASSIVE — Cognitive distinction, clarity

Coord Vectors:
  I → We: Strong (autonomy develops in relational context)
  We → It: Moderate (relatedness enables competence development)
  It → Its: Moderate (competence requires structured environments)
  Its → MoreThanHuman: Moderate (need-supportive contexts)
  MoreThanHuman → Virtual: Emerging (digital autonomy support)

=== Dimensional Analysis ===

Autonomy Field (λ):
  - Volition is the core of self-determination
  - External to internal continuum of motivation
  - Self-endorsement distinguishes autonomous from controlled
  - Choice and agency are essential nutrients

Relatedness Field (ρ):
  - Connection enables authentic expression
  - Secure relationships support autonomy development
  - Internalization occurs through social connection
  - Belonging is a fundamental need

Competence Field (μ):
  - Mastery experiences build self-efficacy
  - Optimal challenge stretches without overwhelming
  - Feedback supports growth orientation
  - Structure enables skill development

Internalization Process (δγ):
  - External regulation → introjection → identification → integration
  - Gradual transformation of motivation quality
  - Growth tendency toward greater autonomy
  - Cycling through stages of self-regulation

=== SWARM INTEGRATION ===

Compatible With:
  - L069_Humanistic_Learning_Theory (growth orientation, self-actualization)
  - L092_Flow_Theory (optimal experience, need satisfaction)
  - L043_Zone_Proximal_Development (optimal challenge, competence)
  - L094_Constructionism (active learning, agency)
  - L095_Experiential_Learning_Cycle (active experimentation)

Tensions With:
  - L064_Information_Processing_Theory (mechanistic, ignores motivation quality)
  - Pure behaviorism (external control vs. autonomy)
  - Extrinsic reward systems (can undermine intrinsic motivation)
  - High-stakes testing (controlling, ego-involving evaluation)

=== PRAXIS NOTES ===

Educational Application:
  - Provide meaningful choices in learning activities
  - Acknowledge and validate student perspectives
  - Give rationale for curriculum requirements
  - Use informational (not controlling) feedback
  - Build warm, supportive relationships
  - Create optimal challenge (not too easy, not too hard)

Organizational Application:
  - Support job crafting and autonomy in role definition
  - Provide growth opportunities and skill development
  - Foster collaborative culture and team connection
  - Minimize controlling surveillance and evaluation
  - Recognize progress and mastery, not just outcomes

Parenting Application:
  - Offer age-appropriate choices
  - Explain reasons for rules and requests
  - Provide unconditional positive regard
  - Support skill development with guidance
  - Maintain warm, responsive relationships

Technology Design:
  - Build autonomy-supportive interfaces (choice, control)
  - Provide competence feedback (progress, mastery)
  - Enable social connection and collaboration
  - Avoid gamification that feels controlling
  - Support intrinsic interest and curiosity

=== ECHO SIGNATURE ===

"Motivation is not a quantity to be increased but a quality to be cultivated—autonomous volition, not controlled compliance, leads to flourishing."

Resonance: High in growth-oriented, need-supportive configurations
Decay: Moderate (requires ongoing need support)
Propagation: Through autonomy-supportive relationships and environments
Mutation: Low (universal needs across contexts)
